{"cursor":"7907","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox Weapon|is_ranged=yes| name=Colt Automatic Rifle |image=\n|caption=Danish LSV (Light Support Weapon) M/04 with optical sight and 100 round\nBeta C-Mag |origin= |type= Squad automatic weapon Light machine gun\n|designer= |design_date= |service= |cartridge=5.56x45mm NATO |action= Direct\nimpingement / Rotating bolt |rate=600-750 round/min |velocity= 991 m/s\n(3,251 ft/s; using the M193 round) 945 m/s (3,100 ft/s; using\nthe M855 round) |range=600 m |weight= 5.78 kg (Unloaded) |length= 1000 mm (39.4\nin) |part_length= 20 in (510 mm) |feed= Various STANAG Magazines. |sights=\nAdjustable front and rear iron |variants= See Text |number=\n|}}\n\n'Colt Automatic Rifle' or 'Colt Light Machine Gun' is a 5.56 mm NATO, open-bolt,\nfull-automatic-only firearm developed by Colt Defense. http:-\n//home.comcast.net/~sfischer397/m16a2oblmg/m16a2oblmgpics/m16a2%20lmg.pdf\nIt is based on the M16A2/A4, and its forward hand-grip has a distinctive squared-\noff shape, pistol grip, carrying handle and integrated bipod.\n\nIt is one of many SAW-type firearms that have been developed from the AR-15.\nOthers include the Colt CMG-1 machine gun and CAR-15 Heavy Assault Rifle.\n","linknr":203,"url":"Colt_Automatic_Rifle","recorded":1372153321,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Colt_Automatic_Rifle&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Colt_Automatic_Rifle&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=